RootCauseAnalysis - INFO -     Result: {'result': 'Looking at the anomaly metrics data, I can see that the most significant issue is with paymentservice-2 showing an extremely high latency spike. From the raw metrics analysis, I observed that paymentservice-2 had a massive latency spike of 71,489ms (over 71 seconds) at 06:11:00, which is the beginning of the fault window.\n\nThe redis-cart-0 pod_processes metric shows the pod was running continuously with a stable value of 1.0 throughout the entire fault period, indicating no pod crashes or restarts.\n\nThe shippingservice also shows elevated latencies, particularly shippingservice-0 with spikes up to 11,518ms, but these are much smaller compared to the paymentservice-2 spike.\n\nThe TiDB component shows increased CPU usage, but I couldn\'t retrieve the raw metrics due to file not found errors.\n\nBased on the analysis, the root cause appears to be the severe latency spike in paymentservice-2 at the start of the fault window.\n\n```json\n{\n  "detected_metric_keys": ["rrt_max", "pod_processes", "cpu_usage"],\n  "affected_components": ["paymentservice-2"],\n  "metric_summary": "paymentservice-2 experienced an extreme latency spike of 71,489ms at 06:11:00, while redis-cart-0 remained stable with pod_processes consistently at 1.0 throughout the fault window.",\n  "time_series_analysis": {\n    "metric_name": "rrt_max",\n    "pattern": "sudden_spike",\n    "critical_timestamps": ["2025-06-11 06:11:00+00:00"],\n    "value_change": "normal (~2000ms) → 71489ms"\n  },\n  "contradictions": [],\n  "next_verification": {\n    "action": "check_logs",\n    "reason": "Extreme latency spike in paymentservice-2 suggests potential database connection issues, external service timeouts, or internal processing bottlenecks",\n    "suggested_metrics": ["error_ratio", "pod_cpu_usage", "pod_memory_working_set_bytes"],\n    "suggested_log_keywords": ["timeout", "database", "connection", "exception", "error"]\n  }\n}\n```'}
